{
  "texts": [
    "Kim et al. [46] and Ahmed et al.",
    "[49] found enhanced resistance to sulfate attack, chloride penetration, and carbonation.",
    "Sankarp and Ramadoss [50] reported a notable reduction in water absorption, improved acid resistance, and increased sulfate resistance when SF was combined with MK.",
    "FASadrmomtazi et al. [42] found that a 30% FA replacement increased concrete permeability by 25% due to additional voids.",
    "However, at a 40% replacement level, durability improved, with reduced chloride ion penetration depths of up to 53% after 180 days."
  ]
